Former Arizona Governor Rose Mofford has passed away, and President Obama released a statement expressing his condolences. Mofford was known for her determination and trailblazing spirit, having overcome being fired from a government position due to her gender to eventually become Secretary of State and then governor. She was the first woman to hold the office of governor in Arizona, inspiring others to follow in her footsteps. The President praised her tireless service and steady leadership, stating that she showed everyone how to respond when faced with discrimination. He extended his thoughts and prayers to Mofford's family and friends as they remember and celebrate her life.